class autoop.core.ml.model.classification.k_nearest_neighbours.KNearestNeighbors(k: int = 3)[source]

Bases: Model

Class that defines K-Nearest Neighbours model.

fit(observations: ndarray, ground_truth: ndarray) → None[source]

Trains the KNN model by storing the input observations and ground truth labels into a dictionary of parameters. :param observations: data to fit on :param ground_truth: labels of the observations

property k: int

Getter for the number of nearest neighbours. The getter is used as this model allows dynamic modification of its hyperparameters, as they are not used in training. :returns: number of nearest neighbours

predict(observations: ndarray) → ndarray[source]

Generates predictions by iterating through each observation and predicting per observation as per the method _predict_single. Returns all the predictions. :param observations: data to make predictions on :returns: predictions made by the model
